us and compassionate thinking.\n\n- Abhijit Naskar, The Film Testament\n|\nOnly with grace, can we reach the goal.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nI am sorry the only outlet for her troubled mind was in clumsy foreplay with an inadequate partner.'He threw the rest of her sandwich at the swinging door as she passed through it.\n\n- Jenny Trout, Ashes to Ashes\n|\nDo business with honesty irrespective of what happens, whatever happens thereafter is correct. But do not start any accounts (karma).\n\n- Dada\n|\nYou are a divine being. You matter, you count. You come from realms of unimaginable power and light, and you will return to those realms.\n\n- Terence\n|\nThe spiritual work builds upon awareness, increases consciousness, transforms it, merges it with the divine, and this is how to reach true spirituality in life.\n\n- Belsebuub, Gazing into the Eternal: Reflections upon a Deeper Purpose to Living\n|\nIntrospection and observation of others are vital for the ongoing good health of our own psyche; watch, learn and tweak as required.\n\n- Sam Owen, 500 Relationships And Life Quotes: Bite-Sized Advice For Busy People\n|\nIf complete and utter chaos was lightning, then he'd be the sort to stand on a hilltop in a thunderstorm wearing wet copper armour and shouting 'All gods are bastards!\n\n- Terry Pratchett, The Color of Magic\n|\nOne thing that makes your confidence echoe over negativity is your patience, understanding, ambitions and trust me it makes your accomplishments astonishing\n\n- Bandile\n|\nThe power of the harasser, the abuser, the rapist depends above all on the silence of women.\n\n- Ursula\n|\nI kept reaching for my muses,my wandering muses, floatingon clouds filled with their passions.”(Muses of Wandering Passions, p. 64)\n\n- Chimnese Davids, Muses of Wandering Passions\n|\nWe sense that ‘normal’ isn’t coming back, that we are being born into a new normal: a new kind of society, a new relationship to the earth, a new experience of being human.\n\n- Charles\n|\nWhen 