l\n|\nGod comes down in the evenings to chat with man, enjoy man's company and find out how man faired in the course of the day.\n\n- Jaachynma N.E. Agu, The Prince and the Pauper\n|\nI have dreamed of our bed as if it were a shore where we would be washed up, not this striped mattress we must cover with sheets. [from 'After an Absence']\n\n- Linda Pastan, The Imperfect Paradise\n|\nPublic schoolboys are not merely conservatives, they are by nature totalitarian reactionaries.\n\n- David\n|\nEveryone has the same amount of hours per day, it’s not that you don’t have enough time, it’s that you don’t have a clear focus\n\n- Bridget\n|\nUntil you do your best, don't try to take a rest. Until you take a leap, don't try to sleep. Until you top, don't try to stop.\n\n- Israelmore Ayivor, Leaders' Ladder\n|\nAnd remember this most of all: when it is darkest, that is when you can see the stars most clearly.\n\n- Kathleen McGowan, The Poet Prince\n|\nA happy childhood can fortify one against the ravages of life, and part of that happiness is found in books, which become our constant companions for the rest of our lives.\n\n- Suzy  Davies, Snugs The Snow Bear\n|\nHe that planteth a tree is a servant of God, he provideth a kindness for many generations, and faces that he hath not seen shall bless him.\n\n- Henry\n|\nTo succeed in life, doing your best is not enough, you should also improve your best.\n\n- Mohith\n|\nI always have the time, the room and the energy for more love.\n\n- Renae A. Sauter, An Empowered Life: Mind/Body/Spirit Empowerment\n|\nAll men make mistakes, but a good man yields when he knows his course is wrong, and repairs the evil. The only crime is pride.\n\n- Sophocles, Antigone\n|\nObserve always that everything is the result of change, and get used to thinking that there is nothing Nature loves so well as to change existing forms and make new ones like them.\n\n- Marcus Aurelius, Meditations\n|\nIn secret we met -In silence I grieve,That thy heart could forget,Thy spirit deceive.If I should meet theeAfter long years,How should I greet thee? -With silence and tears\n\n- George\n|\nI just don't know what I'd do without a brain, Simone!' I say. 'I mean, what's a person without one?\n\n- Randa Abdel-Fattah, Does My Head Look Big In This?\n|\nBeing single isn't a terminal disease.''Try telling that to my mother.\n\n- Alexandra Potter, Do You Come Here Often?\n|\nCreate your own path.Don't blindly follow the massess... because most of the time the 'M' is silent.\n\n- Abhysheq Shukla, The Reflection 'Success or Stress'Choose Wisely\n|\nDefeat anger, stop using it as a shield against truth, and you will find the compassion you need to forgive the people you love.\n\n- Glenn Beck, The 7: Seven Wonders That Will Change Your Life\n|\nIn this world of dreams, drifting off still more; and once again speaking and dreaming of dreams. Just let it be.\n\n- Ryōkan\n|\nThe winning strategy is the one that successfully adapts to the changing circumstances of time, place, and person.\n\n- Rajen Jani, Once Upon A Time: 100 Management Stories\n|\nIn a beautiful morning, walking barefoot to the work through the green fields with the company of the singing birds... and there you shall meet the real happiness!\n\n- Mehmet\n|\nTo become successful, you have to let go of something to get something else of greater value.\n\n- Mensah\n|\nAccentuated plainness and accentuated vice ought to bring about harmony. Beauty lies in harmony, in style, whether it be the harmony of ugliness or beauty, vice or virtue.\n\n- Yevgeny Zamyatin, Islanders And, The Fisher Of Men\n|\nMindfulness may help you gain insight into your role in conflicts with others, it won’t single-highhandedly help you resolve them.\n\n- Sharon Salzberg, Real Love: The Art of Mindful Connection\n|\nThe issue isn't, Am I good enough? No. The issue is, Do I not have any other choice? Will and desire don't matter. Ability doesn't matter. Need is the only thing that matters.\n\n- Dana Spi